<br />
If you want EVERYTHING, well, you&#39;ve gotta pay for it.  :)) <br><BR><font size=1>16:18 03-14-2005</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' valign='top' bgcolor=#C3E3FF><img src='/global/images/premium_icon.gif' border='0' hspace='1' vspace='1'></td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#C3E3FF><font class="bfont"><B><a href="http://www.decktech.net/starwarsccg/main/mpage.php?member=13223">sithborg279™</a></B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#C3E3FF><font class="bfont">I think that is what turned me off.  I like to have various options in what I play. <br><BR><font size=1>16:17 03-14-2005</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' valign='top' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><img src='/global/images/premium_icon.gif' border='0' hspace='1' vspace='1'></td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B><a href="http://www.decktech.net/vs/main/mpage.php?member=1805">Ken B™</a></B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont">The problem with VS, what drives some away, is the &#39;need&#39; to be able to play EVERY team in the game.<br />
<br />
If you do like me--pick and choose--then a box or two will do you fine, then you pick up singles or trade for the extras you need for the &#39;teams&#39; you want to play.<br />
<br />
VS is expensive..but no more expensive than any other CCG, really.  I just spent $200 on Raw Deal, and there are STILL Ultra-Rares from the set I still need, six of them in fact, around $10 each as singles.  <br />
<br />
But instead of buying four more boxes trying to hit them, I buy them as singles.  Once you have all the commons and uncommons you need, it&#39;s silly to buy more boxes.<br />
<br />
I mean, who wants to buy a box and risk MAYBE getting a Beatdown, but instead getting Mr. Sinister, Lady Deathstrike, Juggernaut, e.t.c.?  Or, getting more copies of the power cards you weren&#39;t specifically looking for, like Genosha or Signal Flare if you aren&#39;t playing those teams?<br />
<br />
<br />
Singles in VS are dirt cheap, suprisingly so for how hard it is to pull them.  The "king" is of course Beatdown, which fetches $20 normally.  How many packs is that?  At $3.50, you can&#39;t even get six packs of cards for that.  <br />
<br />
And if you could...how likely is it that there&#39;s a Beatdown in there?<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Philosophy for VS--two to three boxes MAX, trade and buy the singles you need.  Lots of great DT sponsors to get them through too, like Cardagora and Kwyjibo. <br><BR><font size=1>15:58 03-14-2005</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' valign='top' bgcolor=#C3E3FF><img src='/global/images/premium_icon.gif' border='0' hspace='1' vspace='1'></td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#C3E3FF><font class="bfont"><B><a href="http://www.decktech.net/vs/main/mpage.php?member=18468">Torch™</a></B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#C3E3FF><font class="bfont">"it&#39;s like getting kicked in the head with a golf shoe and then asking....please may I have another?"<br />
<br />
yes, but after the first couple of kicks, it numbs the skull enough so each subsequent kick becomes much less painful! <br><BR><font size=1>15:57 03-14-2005</font></TD></TR><TR><td width='4' bgcolor=#FFFFFF>&nbsp;</td><TD ALIGN='LEFT' valign='top' width='70' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont"><B>The Judge</B></font></td><Td valign='top' bgcolor=#FFFFFF><font class="bfont">*I got 1 savage and 1 sabertooth out of 7 boxes.* <br />
